headings.heading: Rank Your School Choices
How did you hear about Wildflower?

Please tell us about the child’s regular adult caregivers, including parents. For each adult, include the name, relationship to the child, and current employment. Please complete for each adult who regularly cares for your child in your home or theirs.
Does your child have any siblings? If so, how old?
Tell us about your child’s disposition. What is your child’s temperament and learning style? What five words would you use to describe your child?

Describe your child’s social style. How quickly or slowly does your child acclimate to new environments? Does your child generally prefer to engage with a few trusted people or to explore new settings independently?

Describe your parenting styles. In what ways are your styles similar? In what ways are they different? (If there is only one parent/guardian involved in child-raising, please disregard the second two parts of this question.)
Describe a typical weekday at your house. If you have a typical morning routine and/or evening routine, please describe those as well.
How does your family spend a typical weekend day?
Describe your ideal school and your ideal relationship between family and school. Why have you chosen Wildflower as a possible match for your family?
What other schools are you considering?
What attracts you to Montessori education? If you have any previous Montessori experience please describe it.
Until what age do you intend on sending your children to Montessori school?

Has your child been referred to or seen a speech or occupational therapist, educational psychologist, or other specialist? Please describe the circumstances. We request this information so as to determine how we might best serve your child.

A key aspect of Wildflower Schools is regular involvement from families and caregivers, on the order of several hours per month. Do you anticipate any challenges to this level of involvement in the school?
Families offer diverse experiences and unique gifts that strengthen school communities. Are there special skills or opportunities your family brings that could enrich our program?
If there is anything else that you would like us to know about your child or family, please use this space to tell us.
